{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"5c9c2a72-2c1e-4997-8277-4228c3c4cad2","content":"**Exit code 8** in MTP means \"zero tests ran\" — MTP treats this as a failure by default, unlike VSTest which returned 0.\n\n**Fix options:**\n\n**Option 1 — CLI flag (per-invocation):**\n```bash\ndotnet test --ignore-exit-code 8\n```\n\n**Option 2 — Environment variable (CI-wide):**\n```bash\nexport TESTINGPLATFORM_EXITCODE_IGNORE=8\ndotnet test\n```\n\n**Option 3 — Project-level (recommended for your case):**\n\nAdd this to your `.csproj` or `Directory.Build.props`:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <TestingPlatformExitCodeOnNoTests>0</TestingPlatformExitCodeOnNoTests>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\nSince your assemblies are *intentionally* empty on some configurations, Option 3 is cleanest — it documents the intent in source control and applies automatically without CI pipeline changes.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"73bfd248-d21d-4b12-945b-2fb678cc8e42","outputTokens":232,"requestId":"E852:28AA9B:27DA8F1:2A50E3C:6A049413"},"id":"326944e7-b279-473e-b3c2-08e1bb5bd4f1","timestamp":"2026-05-13T15:09:15.676Z","parentId":"d6bfa4b6-8675-42e2-83d4-856df1a1e4bd"}
